				"actions": {
					"value": 1
				},
				"category": "offensive",
				"description": {
					"value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The infernal torturer isn't @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.HL2l2VRSaQHu9lUw]{Fatigued} or raging.</p><hr /><p>The infernal torturer enters in a blood induced frenzy, making it more powerful and resilient, at the cost of its defenses:</p><ul><li>The torturer deals 2 additional damage on melee Strikes. This additional damage is halved if its weapon or unarmed attack is agile.</li><li>Its Armor Class is reduced by 1.</li><li>It gains 7 temporary Hit Points.</li></ul><p>Rage lasts for 1 minute, and the torturer can't voluntarily stop raging. When the torturer stop raging, it loses any remaining temporary Hit Points from Rage, and can't gain temporary Hit Points from using the Rage action again for 1 minute.</p><p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feat-effects.Item.MaepXeSHiMoWDm7u]{Effect: Rage Temporary Hit Points Immunity}</p>",
